body:
I just wanted to say

Something that’s been on my mind of late. Somewhere between “I am iron man,” and “I am iron man,” the majority of us grew up. A lot of us became adults in that time, figuring out who we are and were and what we want to become. It may seem obvious, but to me, it’s really amazing. The fact that in between that series of films we have changed and evolved and become something…

And the fact that some didn’t. That some never got to see even the first Avengers film, or the last. Hardcore fans who didn’t live to see the conclusion.

And that’s life, right? Some people live and some people die. But what I find just really amazing is that those of us that made it, we have grown in that space. The space between the beginning and the end. Marvel is amazing because it grew up with us. So many of us were kids when Iron Man came out, and now we’re all grown up.

So I just want to thank my heroes for growing up with me, I guess. And here’s to growing on but never growing away.
